snippet: Whether the cease-fire between Ukraine’s government and separatists lasts will probably be determined by the outcome of negotiations over the political future of the southeastern region.
abstract: Ukrainian government and separatist forces, after months of intensifying combat, sign cease-fire agreement endorsed and laid out by Russian Pres Vladimir V Putin; analysts say that highly tenuous agreement could last depending upon outcome of negotiations over political future of southeastern region.

byline.contributor: Reporting was contributed by Daniel Rzhenetskyy from Kiev; Carlotta Gall from Mariupol, Ukraine; and David M. Herszenhorn and Andrew Roth from Moscow.

lead_paragraph: Whether the cease-fire between Ukraine’s government and separatists lasts will probably be determined by the outcome of negotiations over the political future of the southeastern region.

headline.main: Ukraine Deal Imposes Truce Putin Devised
headline.print_headline: Ukraine Deal Imposes Truce Putin Devised
